&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director, Contracts Counsel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mineralys Therapeutics is seeking an experienced and business-oriented attorney to serve as Director, Contracts Counsel. Reporting to the Chief Legal Officer, this role will lead the drafting, negotiation, and management of a broad range of commercial, clinical, research, and operational agreements that support the company&#39;s strategic objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operating in a fast-paced, pre-commercial biotech environment, this role requires a strong contract negotiation and drafting skills with sound business judgment, a collaborative approach, and a deep understanding of the legal and operational considerations unique to the biotechnology and pharmaceutical industries. This individual will play a key role in optimizing contracting processes, mitigating risk, and supporting Mineralys&#39; continued growth and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft, review, negotiate, and manage a broad range of agreements supporting all aspects of the organization, including master services agreements, consulting agreements, confidentiality agreements, license agreements, clinical trial agreements, manufacturing and supply agreements, and other commercial and operational contracts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with internal constituents, business leaders and cross-functional stakeholders to structure transactions, assess legal and business risks, and facilitate successful business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve contractual disputes and support the management of contract-related legal issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement of contracting processes, templates, policies, and contract management systems to enhance efficiency, consistency, and scalability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with outside counsel and other external advisors as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support additional legal, compliance, corporate, and strategic initiatives within the Legal Department as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;J.D. degree from an accredited law school, strong academic credentials, and active membership in good standing with at least one state bar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 or more years of relevant experience in the biotechnology/pharmaceutical industry and/or equivalent law firm experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated expertise drafting and negotiating complex commercial, clinical, and operational agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written, verbal, negotiation, and interpersonal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to think creatively in confronting new issues and pursuing novel approaches to old problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical, clear and organized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under pressure, meet deadlines and exercise sound business judgment with critical thinking skills and high ethical standards.&lt;/li&gt;
