&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Procurement Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Procurement Specialist will lead sourcing, procurement, and vendor management activities across the organization, with a strong focus on supporting scientific, clinical, and corporate operations. This position will play a key role in ensuring effective and compliant purchasing processes across the business. The ideal candidate will bring experience in the Life Sciences sector and a proven ability to manage complex procurement operations in a high-growth, publicly traded environment. The role will work cross-functionally with key stakeholders across R&amp;amp;D, G&amp;amp;A and Supply Chain teams, ensuring alignment with corporate goals and financial controls. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Principal Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Manage end-to-end procurement lifecycle, including negotiation, contracting, and onboarding, ensuring alignment with internal policies and SOX compliance.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Partner with internal stakeholders to gather requirements, identify cost-saving opportunities, and deliver procurement solutions that add long-term value.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Oversee and optimize the use of procurement platforms, including Tipalti and NetSuite, to improve automation, reporting, and spend visibility.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Collaborate with Finance, Legal, and Compliance to ensure vendor contracts align with corporate policies and risk mitigation strategies.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Support the development of procurement policies and procedures, ensuring scalability and best-in-class governance.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Lead RFPs/RFQs and drive competitive sourcing processes in collaboration with business owners.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Build strong internal partnerships with scientific and clinical teams to understand upcoming needs and proactively manage procurement pipelines.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Provide category-specific market intelligence and cost benchmarking to support strategic decisions.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Continuously seek opportunities to improve procurement processes, reduce costs, and mitigate supply risks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Attributes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Deep knowledge of sourcing, procurement, and vendor management processes within the Life Sciences industries.&lt;br&gt;2. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Strong negotiation and contract management skills.&lt;br&gt;3. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Proficiency with procurement systems, ideally Tipalti and NetSuite.&lt;br&gt;4. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Ability to manage multiple complex projects and priorities in a fast-paced, regulated environment.&lt;br&gt;5. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Excellent interpersonal, communication, and cross-functional collaboration skills.&lt;br&gt;6. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.&lt;br&gt;7. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Experience supporting procurement for R&amp;amp;D, clinical trials and G&amp;amp;A functions.&lt;br&gt;8. &am

